cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the development of machine translation systems for Indian languages using statistical methods and lexical databases. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms, which falls under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the evaluation of the translation quality, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with the development of efficient translation systems, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
